The function $f$ is defined by

$$
\begin{aligned}
f(x) = \left\{\hspace{-0.2em}\begin{array}{rcl}
4x-1 &\text{if}&  x \geq 1, \\[6pt]
-x^2+x+3  &\text{if}&  x<1.
\end{array}\right.\end{aligned}
$$


- Determine whether or not $f$ is continuous at $x = 1$. <span class="marks">[2]</span>


The graph of the function $g$ is obtained by applying the following
transformations
to the graph of $f$:

$$
\begin{aligned}
&\hspace{-5em}\text{a horizontal translation $2$ units to the left, followed by}\\[6pt]
&\hspace{-5em}\text{a reflection in the $x$-axis, followed by}\\[6pt]
&\hspace{-5em}\text{a vertical stretch by a factor of $3$.}
\end{aligned}
$$


- Find $g(x)$. <span class="marks">[4]</span>

